HEADWORD: Rondure
<hw>Ron"dure</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>rondeur</ets> roundness.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A round; a
circle.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Roundness; plumpness.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>High-kirtled for the chase, and what was shown⟦br⟧
Of maiden <qex>rondure</qex>, like the rose half-blown.</q>
<rj><qau>Lowell.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rong</ent>⟦br⟧
